body:
Given the following code ([playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=aee04dbd629e8c238ebffa4166aa0672)):

```rust
use std::ops::Sub;

struct Wrap<T>(T);
impl<T> Sub<Wrap<T>> for Wrap<T>
where
    T: Sub<T, Output = T>,
{
    type Output = Self;

    fn sub(self, other: Self) -> Self {
        Self(self.0 - other.0)
    }
}

fn main() {
    Wrap(()) - Wrap(());
}
```

The current output is:

```
error[[E0369]](https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/error-index.html#E0369): cannot subtract `Wrap<()>` from `Wrap<()>`
  --> src/main.rs:16:14
   |
16 |     Wrap(()) - Wrap(());
   |     -------- ^ -------- Wrap<()>
   |     |
   |     Wrap<()>

```

Ideally the output should look roughly like that:

```
error[[E0369]](https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/error-index.html#E0369): cannot subtract `Wrap<()>` from `Wrap<()>`
  --> src/main.rs:16:14
   |
16 |     Wrap(()) - Wrap(());
   |     -------- ^ -------- Wrap<()>
   |     |
   |     Wrap<()>
   | doesn't satisfy `Wrap<()>: Sub<Wrap<()>>`
...
19 |     Wrap(()).sub(Wrap(()));
   |              ^^^ method cannot be called on `Wrap<()>` due to unsatisfied trait bounds
   |
note: trait bound `(): Sub<()>` was not satisfied
  --> src/main.rs:9:8
   |
7  | impl<T> Sub<Wrap<T>> for Wrap<T>
   |         ------------     -------
8  | where
9  |     T: Sub<T, Output = T>,
   |        ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ unsatisfied trait bound introduced here
note: trait bound `<() as Sub<()>>::Output = ()` was not satisfied
  --> src/main.rs:9:15
   |
7  | impl<T> Sub<Wrap<T>> for Wrap<T>
   |         ------------     -------
8  | where
9  |     T: Sub<T, Output = T>,
   |               ^^^^^^^^^^ unsatisfied trait bound introduced here
```

That’s only a problem for arithmetic traits: this code gives a detailed error ([playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=a0172e879f6c4b254c517fe70a7d6b21)):
```rust
trait Sub<T> {
    type Output;
    fn sub(self, other: T) -> Self::Output;
}

struct Wrap<T>(T);
impl<T> Sub<Wrap<T>> for Wrap<T>
where
    T: Sub<T, Output = T>,
{
    type Output = Self;

    fn sub(self, other: Self) -> Self {
        Self(self.0.sub(other.0))
    }
}

fn main() {
    Wrap(()).sub(Wrap(()));
}
```
